Hello World!

So you want to know more about me?

But let's start with where I started

I first started to become interested in computers when I was at the young age of 10. From there I go involved in the modding community in Counter Strike Source, an online first person shooter, where you can host your own server and make it into anything you want. I was trying to have my own server with an RPG mod that was written JavaScript. I ran into many issues since I had no idea how to program, and no idea where to start. It eventually lead me to researching and learning what I needed to run the mod and my desire to research and learn was sparked.

I was originally interested in studying mechincal engineering, since I love making things. From designing, to prototyping, to making the final product, I loved every second of it. I then became interested in computer science since the aspects of problem solving, designing, and coming to a magnificent solution. I had no clear direction of what I specifically wanted to do so I wanted to be versitile.

Then I found myself in the web application development class at Grand Valley State University. I fell in love with it. The ability to develop an application that is robust and used everywhere amazed me. I needed to know more, I wanted to know more, I had to learn more. Thus resulting in where I am today. The ability to pick up a language, or framework in a couple hours and use it to develop a web app as long as I had documentation handy. I've developed full stack applications such as a basic ToDo app with ASP.NET, an achievement tracker with Vue, Firebase Database, and Firebase auth, and a JAMstack website using React and Next.js.
